        Animal studies have suggested a link between sleep and metabolism [<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">31,32</NUMEX>]. In <ENAMEX TYPE="ANIMAL">rats</ENAMEX>,
        prolonged, complete sleep deprivation increased both food intake and energy expenditure.
        The net effect was weight loss and, ultimately, death [<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">33</TIMEX>]. Rats fed a high
